README:

Includes the main resources I have looked into throughout the development of the project as well as explanations of how I approached the problem.

Makefile:

Includes commands to clean, make and tar the project. Clean gets rid of the executable along with any .o files and the tarball. dist, tarballs the project into the zip format specified by the spec. make builds the executable with the flags specified in the spec along with -g for debugging.

